snippet.textDisplay: I came back to my hometown the day before yesterday, and there was an unexpected gathering of some of our old classmates. She was there. Seeing her brought back so many memories. Since yesterday, I've been listening to this song on repeat—the song I used to sing for her. Each word feels heavier now, carrying all the emotions I never got to express. I feel every moment we shared and everything I lost.
